    "Dauer later added a schematic approach to Brown's observations by stating that prevention can be applied at three intervals to manage legal risk, i.e., before, during, and after damage occurs [32].",
    "Dauer's systematic analysis resulted in a matrix, which Barton called Dauer's matrix [23].",
    "Barton then refined it considerably [41,42].Currently, most literature focusses on the mindset and application of Preventive Law.",
    "The authors do so in various domains, one of which is iContracts [7] (see Definition 5).",
    "Indeed, there are exceptions that only partially help people prevent legal problems."
